Q: Apply Different CSS Background Color Last Three Rows of Table A: <p>An alternative to @Arun's good answer is to use <code>:nth-last-child()</code></p>
<p>Like so:</p>
<pre class="lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>table&gt;tbody:last-of-type&gt;tr:nth-last-child(1),
table&gt;tbody:last-of-type&gt;tr:nth-last-child(2),
table&gt;tbody:last-of-type&gt;tr:nth-last-child(3) {
  background-color: #fcba7a;
}
</code></pre>
<p>Note that I've also repaired your <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> HTML such that all rows are now in <code>&lt;thead&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code>, and the <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> have been moved out.</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
